  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The governing requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification method for hemolysis QoI validation; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study drawing on retrospective clinical pump-flow data rather than a purpose-designed controlled bench experiment. The narrative presents the observational dataset as functionally equivalent to controlled experimentation, citing its breadth across five operating points and the use of Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation, but the structured activityType field records 'observational-study', not 'controlled-experiment'. This inference-method mismatch constitutes the W-AR-03 weakener under review.",
