      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-observational-result",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against retrospective clinical pump data",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values from the CFD model were compared against retrospective clinical pump-flow measurements collected across five operating points (2–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM). Agreement within ±18% was observed at four of five operating points. Monte Carlo uncertainty envelopes (n=2000 samples) encompassed all measured values. The activity is described as providing experimental grounding for the hemolysis QoI, and the assessment team concluded that the breadth of the dataset and the rigorous uncertainty propagation rendered the evidence substantively equivalent to a controlled bench experiment. The structured record, however, classifies this activity as an observational study.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/retrospective-pump-flow-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "name": "Retrospective clinical pump-flow observational study",
        "activityType": "observational-study",
        "description": "Retrospective collection and analysis of clinical pump-flow data from three hospital sites operating the FDA generic centrifugal pump under VAD indications. Data were not collected under controlled experimental protocols; operating conditions were determined by clinical need rather than experimental design. No randomisation, blinding, or controlled perturbation of independent variables was performed. The dataset spans five nominal operating points but with uncontrolled co-variates including patient haematocrit, anticoagulation regime, and ambient temperature."
      }
    }
  ],
  "requirements": [
