      "name": "Hemolysis QoI verification method requirement",
      "description": "For MRL-5 Class III VAD applications, absolute hemolysis index predictions must be verified against data generated by a controlled experiment in which independent variables (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid haematocrit) are systematically varied under laboratory conditions with appropriate controls and replication. Observational or retrospective datasets do not satisfy this requirement because confounding variables cannot be isolated.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
